The African National Congress (ANC) says it will meet with the party s veterans who have been calling for President Jacob Zuma to resign. ANC has noted the comments made in the public domain by veterans of our movement expressing concern about developments within the country and the ANC the party s secretary-general Gwede Mantashe said on Tuesday. The ANC reiterates our commitment to frank open and constructive engagement with all parties and individuals who wish to engage and work with us to strengthen the organisation so as to deliver effectively on the aspirations of the South African people. Accordingly the NWC has resolved to constitute itself as a delegation to meet with the veterans who have indicated the need for a platform of engagement. A date for the meeting is yet to be set Mantashe said. TMG Digital